Alembic migrations for the SQLite DB at ./travel_planner.db.

The first migration (0c7a67724fda_baseline.py) captures the schema as it
stood at the start of Phase G. From now on, every schema change should be
a new migration file generated via:

    alembic revision -m "describe change"

…and applied with:

    alembic upgrade head

Existing dev/prod DBs that already had the schema (created by
database.init_db running at startup) need a one-time:

    alembic stamp head

…to mark them as up-to-date without re-running the baseline CREATEs.
The repo's dev DB (src/travel_planner.db) was stamped on 2026-05-05.

init_db() still runs at Flask startup as a safety net for fresh dev setups.
It will be retired once all schema management goes through migrations.